value.title: Biden's Keystone pipeline cancellation was 'political reward' for left-wing supporters: Georgia AG

value.title: Wall Street Journal: Trump might be acquitted, but won't live down 'disgraceful conduct'
value.excerpt: The Wall Street Journal’s editorial board wrote that while the Senate may acquit former President Trump over the deadly riot at the U.S. Capitol, “he won’t live down his disgraceful conduct.”

value.title: Hillary Clinton: If Trump is acquitted, it's 'because the jury includes his co-conspirators'
value.excerpt: Hillary Clinton weighed in on former President Donald Trump's second impeachment trial this week, suggesting in a tweet that if the Senate ultimately votes to acquit him, it will only be because "the jury includes his co-conspirators."

value.title: Suu Kyi aide, electoral officials arrested in Myanmar, Biden approves sanctions
